abstract: The European Commission conducted antitrust raids Tuesday at the Munich offices of Intel, the world’s largest chip maker, and of retailers selling products made by the company, the commission and the chip maker said.
lead_paragraph: The European Commission conducted antitrust raids Tuesday at the Munich offices of Intel, the world’s largest chip maker, and of retailers selling products made by the company, the commission and the chip maker said.

headline.main: E.U. Antitrust Regulators Raid Intel Offices
